Police in Barberton arrested three suspects on Saturday morning. They were arrested in possession of pure heroin,which according to the police worth R50 million, on the R40 road between the Jathira and Badplaas turnoff. The suspects are believed to be from Mozambique. Col Johan Engelbrecht said that the packaged drugs were manufactured and packaged in Afghanistan, then transported by boat to Mozambique and were on the way to Gauteng. The suspects are expected to appear in court soon.